    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - INSTALL - UNIVERSAL JOINT COMPANION FLANGE
        OR YOKE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>UNIVERSAL JOINT COMPANION FLANGE OR YOKE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lock the transmission in gear by engaging two sliding clutches at the same time (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021k2">Figure 202</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021k2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021k2" filename="../figg13/G13021K2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 202. Lock Transmission In Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install an output yoke or flange. Tighten the nut to 450 to 500 ft-lbs. (610 to 678 N&#8226;
                m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021k3">Figure 203</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021k3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021k3" filename="../figg13/G13021K3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 203. Install Output Yoke Or Flange</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
